# Copy to server/.env and fill in. Omit entirely to use the SQLite dev default.
#
# --- Local Postgres (Docker) ---------------------------------------------
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://dromo:dromo@db:5432/dromo
#
# --- Supabase (Global Track Table backend) -------------------------------
# Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> Database -> Connection string.
# Use the *Session pooler* (it supports prepared statements, unlike the
# Transaction pooler) and the SQLAlchemy asyncpg driver prefix: swap the
# `postgresql://` prefix Supabase shows for `postgresql+asyncpg://` and drop
# any `?sslmode=...` arg -- the app enables TLS automatically for supabase hosts.
#
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres.<project-ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
#
# If you must use the Transaction pooler (port 6543), append
# `?prepared_statement_cache_size=0` -- pgbouncer transaction mode rejects
# the prepared statements SQLAlchemy's asyncpg dialect caches by default.
